==English==

===Etymology===
Virtual [[loanword]] from French, [[dénouement]], itself derived from Old French ''[[denoer]]'' ("to [[untie]]"), and {{Lat}} ''[[nodus]]'' ("[[knot]]").

===Noun===
'''denouement'''
#the end [[result]], [[conclusion]], or [[resolution]], especially of a [[plot]] or [[story]]
#:''In the '''denouement''' of the mystery, we learn that the butler did it.''

